{
  "stem": "26111.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And these would be large apartments, typically in buildings about maybe four or five stories high, at most.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "About the second or third floor, I would think.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He had been a doctor for quite a few years before I was born, a pediatrician.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he had his-- now the next apartment that we had, I know that he had his practice, which was quite customary in Europe at that time.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had his, his, his consulting rooms in the apartment.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One part of the apartment was set aside for that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was separate enough so that family and patients didn't get mixed up with each other.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In that [SIGHS] apartment, on the Munzstrasse when I was smaller, I cannot tell you whether he was actually in the-- whether he, he had his consulting rooms, his practice, inside the apartment, or whether he had separate consulting rooms.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The second one that I recall is a much longer name.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it is Weissgerber Strasse, which is W-E-I-S-S-G-E-R-B-E-R.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And a Gerber is German-- the word 'Gerber' is German for tanner, tanning leather, a tanner.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Weissgerber, I have no idea.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They must have tanned something white.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But anyway, this, as many other street names, was called after a guild, presumably from many, many years ago.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] He was a very busy man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was a very intellectual man, also highly intelligent and highly sensitive, read a lot.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I guess I inherited my love of books from him, at least I like to think so.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was somewhat distant-- loving, yes-- but the time that we spent with him was, obviously, under the circumstances, far, far less than the time that we spent with my mother.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
